cast.text:
It's pretty hard to find onchain activity that is directly associated with farcaster users, since you not only need to index onchain activity but also to index farcaster activity. Our first product that solves this a webhook payload that triggers whenever a farcaster user completes a trade. You can filter webhook deliveries by neynar user score, a list of fids, or minimum trade amount denominated in USDC! Try it out either via the api or the dev portal https://docs.neynar.com/reference/publish-webhook#body-subscription-trade-created https://dev.neynar.com/webhook/create

big ups to @quazia and @arpita-205 for this one

I‚Äôve been on Farcaster for like 1.5 years now - essentially every day

Here‚Äôs what I‚Äôve observed about this space 

People seem to forget to zoom out and look at progress of this space

I feel like people expect the Farcaster team to create $DEGEN and $CLANKER moments out of thin air, when in fact it was the community who made those things

We are so early in this space that people make fun of us still on X - I see that as a good thing. It confirms being early. 

Beyond simply making money off rewards or tips, you are building a dope network of people. I think in 10 years we will all be called the cabal lol (including @geoffgolberg)

I‚Äôm not technical, but I do have good intuition. My intuition says to keep going. Keep building on Farcaster and connecting. It will be worth it :)

text:
I don't fully understand what I'm looking at when I open the search page and wallet.

This isn't a criticism of the team's recent updates - just a public confession of my ignorance to all of you who seem to swim through all of this like fish in water.

I mostly ignore tokens here - not out of cynicism, but confusion. When I click on token pages, even popular ones like $DEGEN, I struggle to understand what the project actually is. (The bottom of the $DEGEN page says "No casts about this token yet.")

After a few months on Farcaster, I feel I'm missing out on an interesting way to support interesting projects - beyond donating via Crowdfund. The terms I'm seeing blend together in my eyes: "app coins, "memecoins", "creator coins", "streamer coins" and things just called "coins." Plus "scam coins" flagged by the community.

This cast is not a request for trading tips. I'm looking for your personal perspectives or reading recommendations to understand what drives this activity everyone seems so fluent in and what makes Farcaster a special place to do it. What motivates you to buy tokens here?

I'm having a boomer moment and want to overcome it. Thank you.

text:
This is Rosalie, she has Rett Syndrome.

Reverse Rett is a charity funding research to reverse the symptoms that come from a mutated gene. 

These symptoms limit Rosalie and thousands of others from being able to use their body to its fullest potential. It often leads to breathing issues and seizures and early deaths, particularly for boys. 

I'm running for Reverse Rett on Sunday at the Royal Parks Half Marathon. If you're able and willing to sponsor me, you can do so here: https://www.justgiving.com/page/phil-royal-parks-reverse-rett
